How to install git on EC2 instance


1.	Create an EC2 instance with Amazon Linux 2 with internet access
2.	Connect to your instance using putty

3.	Perform a quick update on your instance:
sudo yum update -y

4.	Install git in your EC2 instance
sudo yum install git -y
To install Git in a different platform, please refer below git documentation
https://git-scm.com/book/en/v1/Getting-Started-Installing-Git

